 global citizenship ? Retrieved November 30,2003,from http://www.oxfam.org.uk/coolplanet/teachers/globciti/whatis.htmOxfam(1997b) . Key elements of global citizenship .Retrieved November 30,2003,from http://www.oxfam.org.uk/coolplanet/teachers/globciti/key.htmPatrick, J. J. (1997). Global trends in civic education for democracy . Eric Document Reproduction Service No. ED410176.Parker, W.,Grossman,D.,Kubow,P.,Kurth-Schai,R.& Nakayama,S.(2000). InCogan, J. J.& Derricott, R.（Eds.）.Citizenship for the 21st century. London: Kogan Page Limited.Parker, W. C. (2001). Toward enlightened political engagement.In:W.STANLEY(Ed.).Critical issues in social studies research .Greenwich,Information Age Press.Pratte, R. (1988). The Civic imperative: Examining the need for civic education .New York : Teachers College Press.Print, M. (1999). Civic education and civil society in the Asia-Pacific . In M. Print, J. Ellickson Brown, & A. Baginda(Eds.). Civic education for civil society.London: Asean Academic Press. pp.9-18.Print, M. & David, C. (2003). Toward understanding of social capital and citizenship education, Cambridge Fournal of Education , 33(1),pp.124-148.Potter, J. (2002). The challenge of education for active citizenship .Education & Training , 44 , pp.57-66.Rawls,J.(1971). A theory of justice. Massachusettes:Harvard Univeraity Press.Rawls,J.(1993).Political liberalism. New York:Columbia University Press.Rubin,A.,& Babbie,E.(1993).Research methods for social work(2nd ed.).Pacific Grove,CA:Brooks/Cole.Sandel, M.(1982). Liberalism and the limits of justice. London: Cambridge University press.Sandel, M.(1983). Liberalism and the limits of justice. London: Cambridge University press.Smith, A. (2003). Global challenges for citizenship education. Retrieved September 21,2004,from http://www.global-citizenship.org/pdf/research/Alan%20Smith%20-%20Global%20Challen.pdfSteenbergen, B. V.﹙1994﹚. Toward a global ecological citizen. In﹕Steenbergen, B.V. ﹙Ed.﹚. The condition of citizenship .Lo